The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 February is 212,787 (24,524.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 February, there were 9,943 new confirmed cases (1,146.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 January, there were 11,275 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 12% (1,332 fewer cases).
